---
description: "Context for project reporting files — workflows, reporting config, ROVO docs. Triggered when editing reporting workflow or project-reporting/ directory."
globs: .github/workflows/*report*,project-reporting/**/*
alwaysApply: false
---

When the user edits files matching this rule:

- ROVO-first: GitHub Actions only schedules and signals; Jira + Slack delivery is in Atlassian ROVO automation.
- Workflow source of truth: [ReportingAgent](https://github.com/codeandtheory/ReportingAgent) template via `template-manifest.json`.
- Re-run **Set up project reporting** to refresh from latest ReportingAgent `main`.
- Never commit webhook URLs, tokens, or API keys.
- GitHub secrets: `ROVO_AUTOMATION_WEBHOOK_URL`, `ROVO_AUTOMATION_WEBHOOK_TOKEN` (optional).
- GitHub variables: `ROVO_TARGET_PROJECT_KEY`, `ROVO_TARGET_SLACK_CHANNEL`.

For full setup workflow, read `.cursor/skills/project-reporting-kit/SKILL.md`.
